  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      - The use of sunscreen on the first day after fractional ablative skin resurfacing may
      reduce the risk of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      -  The use of sunscreen on the first day after fractional ablative skin resurfacing may
           reduce the risk of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (PIH)

        -  Therefore, we conducted the study to evaluate the efficacy of the use of sunscreen on
           the first day after fractional ablative skin resurfacing in reducing the risk of PIH.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
